 the current upper bound and give some number of upper bounds for\nthe closed distinguishing choice number by using the Combinatorial\nNullstellensatz. We show that it is $\\mathbf{NP}$-complete to decide for a\ngiven planar subcubic graph G, whether dis[G]=2. Also, we prove that for every\n$k\\geq 3$, it is {\\bf NP}-complete to decide whether $dis[G]=k$ for a given\ngraph G\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Nov 2016 04:07:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-11"}
