ic haze. For the\nparticles in the storm clouds, which we assume to be composed of methane ice\nparticles, we find that their mean radii must be ~0.5 micron. We find that the\nhigh clouds have low integrated opacity, and that \"streamers\" reminiscent of\nthunderstorm anvils are confined to levels deeper than 1 bar. These results\nargue against vigorous moist convective origins for the cloud features.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Nov 2016 11:04:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-22"}
